alls of the world's largest agricultural biotechnology companies to field trials of hybrid maize in Kenya, Eddens shows how the Green Revolution fails to address global inequalities. Seeding Empire insists that eradicating hunger in a world of climate crisis demands thinking beyond the Green Revolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aClimatic changeszAfrica. 0aEconomic assistance, AmericanzAfrica. 0aGreen RevolutionxHistory. 0aGreen RevolutionzAfrica. 0aTransgenic plantszAfrica. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520395329?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520395329423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520395329/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles